2013.09.17 Studied on GIT

1. First, create the git repository on the web !
https://github.com/gitytakahas
-> create a new repo (right top menu)

2. git clone
git clone https://github.com/gitytakahas/YutaMacro <Name of the directory>

3. work on the directory and register files 
git add <files> 
git add . (will be all)

4. commit
git commit -m "Create YutaMacro, First commit"

5. git push
git push -u origin master


=== branch
1. git branch issue1
2. git checkout issue1 => Move to the issue1 branch

--> or in short, git checkout -b <branch>

3. git merge master => Merge branch
4. git branch -d issue1 => Remove branch


=== Status check commands
git status == show status
git describe --tags (tag check) == show tags
git log == show history 
git log --graph --oneline == show history in a easy-see way
git log --decorate
git branch == show branches


=== tag
git tag apple
git tag
git tag -am "this is banana" banana
git tag -d apple => Delete tag


=== PROBABLY NOT USED !!

mkdir YutaMacro
git init => Create .git directory under the working tree
git add .
git commit -m "xxx"
git remote add origin https://github.com/gitytakahas/YutaMacro
git push -u origin master


See more info at https://github.com/gitytakahas/Test